We have recommended the following:

Direct the Municipal Agriculture Officer to secure a Memorandum of Agreement between the LGU and the beneficiary farmers or any document to prove that the above mentioned animals were already distributed to the LGU’s beneficiaries as basis in adjusting the books of the LGU;

Enjoin the Municipal Accountant to trace the undetermined livestock amounting to ₱73,900 and reconcile its books with the records in the Municipal Agriculture Office. Further, to credit the account if proven that these animals were already distributed;

Instruct the Municipal Accountant to reconcile the list of distribution of the agricultural goods with that of the accounting records and prepare journal entry voucher to recognize as expense the corresponding amount of agricultural goods that were already distributed; and

Enjoin to Municipal Agriculturist, in future dispersal programs of the LGU, to furnish the Office of the Municipal Accountant of the list once the agricultural goods and animals are distributed for the Municipal Accountant to evaluate and adjust the books of the LGU.

Recommendations:

We have recommended the following:

a. Prioritize the verification of the submitted liquidation reports and ensure that correct accounting entries shall be used upon recording;


b. Refrain from granting of additional cash advance unless the previous cash advance given is first settled or proper accounting thereof is made;


c. Demand immediate settlement or liquidation of cash advances and/or cause the withholding of the amount due from the concerned officials and employees to compel them to settle their accounts. Management may resort to legal action if no settlement has been made after sending three (3) demand letters;

d. Demand full refund of excess of cash advance upon liquidation; and


e. File a request for authority to write-off for the accounts that are deemed dormant and liquidation is futile, to be guided by the procedures contained in COA Circular 2016-005 dated December 19, 2016.

Recommendations:

We have recommended the following:

Expedite implementation and completion of the projects in accordance with the guidelines stated in memorandum of agreement with source agency for the immediate benefit to constituents, if MOA is not available, ask a copy from the source agencies so funds could be properly disbursed;

Instruct the Municipal Accountant and Municipal Treasurer to conduct reconciliation of records with source agency for proper recognition of fund transfer balances and full liquidation;

Instruct the Municipal Treasurer to return to source agencies unexpended fund balances on all completed projects and consummated activities, and for the Municipal Accountant to draw journal entry voucher to record the return as evidenced by the source agency’s official receipt, otherwise to request for authority to realign said balances for other priority projects; and

Enjoin the Municipal Engineer to verify the status of projects with corresponding Construction-in-Progress (CIP) accounts of more than 90% of the amount received from source agencies if already completed and provide the Municipal Accountant with copies of Certificate of Completion and Certificate of Final Acceptance. The Municipal Accountant shall then reconcile records and liquidate with source agencies, and draw journal entry vouchers to close the liability account and to reclassify the CIP to appropriate PPE account taking into considerations the LGU counterpart in the Trust Liabilities.

